sentence: In technology stocks news, software provider Salesforce.com ( CRM ) shares jumped nearly 13% after reporting as-expected Q4 results and setting its FY 2016 guidance in line with the Street view.
And, 3D Systems ( DDD ) was lower in pre-market trade after missing Q4 estimates and posting cautious guidance.
The printing company posted Q4 revenue of $187.4 million, versus $154.8 million in the previous year quarter.
This was lower than the $202.3 million Capital IQ consensus.
